article.headline: Bethune-Cookman holds off Morgan State 65-58
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Ricky Johnson scored 20 points and DeLino Dear had 11 with a career-high 16 rebounds to lead Bethune-Cookman to a 65-58 win over Morgan State on Monday. The Wildcats (6-13, 2/3 Mid-Eastern Athletic) finished 24 of 27 from the foul line, including 15 of 16 in the second half with the miss coming with 19 seconds left. Johnson was 9 of 9 from the line and Brandon Stewart hit 6 of 6 while scoring 11 points. Zech Smith scored 13 points and grabbed 14 rebounds for the Bears (4-16, 2-4), who were 11 of 20 from the foul line. Cedric Blossom and Blake Bozeman had 12 points apiece. Johnson had 14 points as Bethune-Cookman took a 31-26 lead at halftime. Morgan State got within one with six minutes left but the Wildcats held them off and then made seven free throws in the final 1:37.
